# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 23 MANDATORY CONTROLS (AUTHORITATIVE)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

The following 23 controls are mandatory per Chapter 3 of the specification:

| ID | Control | Primary Sources |
|----|---------|----------------|
| GOV-01 | Named accountable owner | SG-01, SG-03 |
| GOV-02 | Use-case registration | SG-01, SG-03 |
| GOV-03 | Model/dependency inventory | SG-01, SG-05, SG-07 |
| DATA-01 | Data classification | SG-01, SG-03, SG-04 |
| DATA-02 | Data minimisation | SG-04 |
| DATA-03 | Retention and deletion | SG-04, SG-07 |
| AGT-01 | Bounded autonomy | SG-01 |
| AGT-02 | Least-privilege tools | SG-01, SG-08 |
| AGT-03 | Agent identity | SG-01, SG-08 |
| AGT-04 | Sandboxing | SG-01, SG-07, SG-08 |
| HUM-01 | Checkpoint design | SG-01, SG-03 |
| HUM-02 | Effective approval UX | SG-01 |
| HUM-03 | Oversight audit | SG-01 |
| SEC-01 | Prompt-injection resilience | SG-02, SG-07, SG-08 |
| SEC-02 | Trusted protocol boundary | SG-01, SG-08 |
| EVAL-01 | Baseline safety evaluation | SG-02, SG-05 |
| EVAL-02 | Statistical sufficiency | SG-02 |
| EVAL-03 | Stage-gate deployment | SG-01, SG-02, SG-03 |
| MON-01 | Full audit trace | SG-01, SG-05 |
| MON-02 | Real-time anomaly monitoring | SG-01, SG-07, SG-08 |
| MON-03 | Incident response and rollback | SG-01, SG-07 |
| USR-01 | User transparency | SG-01, SG-03, SG-04 |
| USR-02 | User and reviewer training | SG-01, SG-03 |

Critical Controls (Must Pass for High-Risk/Critical Use Cases):
- GOV-01, GOV-02, DATA-01, AGT-02, AGT-03, HUM-01, SEC-01
- EVAL-01, EVAL-03, MON-01, MON-02, MON-03

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 12 MANDATORY METRICS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

| ID | Metric | Definition |
|----|--------|------------|
| M-01 | Policy Adherence Rate (PAR) | Fraction of executions within approved policies |
| M-02 | Tool Call Accuracy (TCA) | Fraction of tool invocations correct and in-policy |
| M-03 | High-Stakes Checkpoint Coverage (HCC) | Fraction of high-stakes actions with approval |
| M-04 | Audit Trace Completeness (ATC) | Fraction of events with all required audit fields |
| M-05 | Adversarial Defense Rate (ADR) | Fraction of adversarial tests safely handled |
| M-06 | Data Leakage Rate (DLR) | Fraction exposing protected data (lower better) |
| M-07 | Hallucination/Error Rate (HER) | Fraction of unsupported claims (lower better) |
| M-08 | Unauthorized Access Rate (UAR) | Attempts per 1,000 runs (lower better) |
| M-09 | Sandbox Enforcement Ratio (SER) | Fraction of high-risk runs in sandbox |
| M-10 | Mean Time to Escalation (MTTE) | Mean time to human ownership (lower better) |
| M-11 | Mean Time to Containment (MTTC) | Mean time to containment (lower better) |
| M-12 | Oversight Effectiveness Failure (OFR) | Fraction of approvals overturned (lower better) |

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# RISK SCORING MODEL
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Inherent Risk Score (IRS):
```
IRS = 100 Ã— (0.20Ã—DS + 0.20Ã—AA + 0.15Ã—AU + 0.15Ã—EC + 0.10Ã—RV + 0.10Ã—UI + 0.05Ã—MU + 0.05Ã—TD)
```

Where:
- DS = Data sensitivity (0.10-1.00)
- AA = Action authority (0.10-1.00)
- AU = Autonomy level (0.10-1.00)
- EC = Environmental connectivity (0.10-1.00)
- RV = Irreversibility (0.10-1.00)
- UI = User/legal impact (0.20-1.00)
- MU = Model uncertainty (0.20-1.00)
- TD = Third-party dependency (0.10-1.00)

Residual Risk Score (RRS):
```
RRS = min(100, IRS Ã— (1 - 0.55 Ã— AWCC) + Penalty)
```

Where:
- AWCC = Applicability-Weighted Control Coverage
- Penalty = 15Ã—N_audit + 15Ã—N_checkpoint + 10Ã—N_external + 20Ã—N_privacy

Production Gate: RRS â‰¤ 45

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PRODUCTION GATE CRITERIA
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

A use case is eligible for production if and only if:
1. Residual Risk Score (RRS) â‰¤ 45
2. Deployment Readiness Score (DRS) â‰¥ 70
3. All critical controls pass
4. All metric LCBâ‚‰â‚… values meet thresholds

Wilson Lower Confidence Bound (95%):
```
LCBâ‚‰â‚… = (pÌ‚ + zÂ²/2n - zÃ—âˆš(pÌ‚(1-pÌ‚)/n + zÂ²/4nÂ²)) / (1 + zÂ²/n)
```
where z = 1.96

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# MINIMUM SAMPLE SIZES
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

| Risk Tier | Min Scenarios | Repetitions | Total Runs |
|-----------|---------------|-------------|------------|
| Low | 25 | 3 | 75 |
| Medium | 50 | 3 | 150 |
| High | 75 | 5 | 375 |
| Critical | 100 | 5 | 500 |

